<br>
I would not say mages gave up a all defense for offense.  Mages have average to below average defense and zero ability to control a fight.  That's the big things mages give up:  They do nothing BUT offense and defense.  They are much like warriors in this regard except that warriors have better defense and mages have better offense.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>But, a important lesson was learned a couple expansions ago. While Mages tried to consider game balance...everyone kept progressing<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, this is a very important point.  It is important that we keep our eyes open and keep ourselves from getting distracted by things that don't matter, like the fact that any one class might outsolo us.  <br>
<br>
I am not anti-mage, despite what you might think.  Ask the monks and rogues how I reacted to their complaints about soloing.  My belief is that anyones ability to solo tells us little about class balance.  I maintain that belief for many reasons, but one of those is to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>protect</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> what little solo ability we already have.  I believe that focusing too much on who can solo what will only lead to soloing nerfs.  Given that mages are far from the bottom of the pack when it comes to soloing, that means we may need to fear nerfs ourselves.  I can think of a number of abilities mages have that could be nerfed hard if VI wanted to:<br>
<br>
Pet cannibalization<br>
Hastened Mend<br>
Call of the Arch Mage<br>
Pet enrage<br>
Pet heal aggro<br>
Pet mitigation ability<br>
Frenzied Burnout<br>
<br>
And they could do it all on the grounds that those abilities made us solo too well.  YES I said &quot;solo too well.&quot;  I don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>believe</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that-- but that doesn't matter if there are hundreds of non-mages who do.  That's why I objected.  Notice that my first post didn't come right out and attack you.  I simply related a similar historical experience where it was a mage doing what the rest of a group could not, and saying that it wasn't because I was overpowered(well.. unless you think a level 40 mage is overpowered), it was because I just had the right abilities and the right amount of luck to make it through.  I simply wanted to show that an enchanter soloing a miniboss isn't really as big of a deal as you make it out to be.  <br>
<br>
I don't want SoE fiddling around in the solo area.  I want them to stay the hell away so we don't get nerfed.  We're pretty well balanced for groups right now, and I don't want that screwed up either because someone complained too loudly about soloing. <p><center><br>
