<br>
I was with a chanter when she first got Dire charm.  We duo'ed in the Arena and honestly I didn't do much at all.  We pulled every mob there excepting Vindi and duly owned it with that dire charmed pet spear-heading the conquest.  I was mainly there to help take adds (she can root them otherwise) and to add some more damage here and there.  She heads to Kael arena when bored and takes out Protectors of Zek and every other mob in the Arena she can get to.  <br>
<br>
But, that's not the subject of the post.  <br>
<br>
Not to defend charm fighting, but the enchanter and druid versions of charm have been greatly nerfed down from their original state.  Several of our guild enchanters have CoD and have reported they can't by themselves solo one of the BoT minis because of the great chance of charm breaking while clearing to them and during the actual fight.  Duoing them is quite easy though, I'll admit.  Since the nerf, most chanters have to have nerves of steel to really go after the minis or even the named alone.  Now on the subject of mage charming... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It still has it's -100 built in debuff, lasts 20.5 minutes max (is consistent in lasting 12-15 minutes at a time easily) and all our buffs work on them (burnout &gt; any comparable haste buff in the game) as well as Frenzied Burnout.  I don't personally have Call of the Arch Mage, but just from watching it in action I will agree that it is a heck of powerful spell.  <br>
<br>
That being said, of course I'd hate to see charm nerfed... There's not much Verant can really do to charm short of killing the duration down to a few minutes and doing away with any sort of resist adjustments the spells have.  In essence, that would cause too big of an uproar for them to really want to fool with.  In it's current state, it has nerfed down soloing the uber stuff a bit (aside from the beforementioned chanters with nerves of steel).   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
