<br>
Have the enchanter try it 10 times.  Charm and attempt a mini-boss in BOT, heck any mob in BOT.  Charm will break midfight 8 or 9 out of 10 times.  In BOT since mobs summon = dead enchanter almost every time.   A high end enchanter may have the HP + Channelling Ability + cast time focus items to get a charm through and live, but most are dead every time in BOT.<br>
<br>
So ? Solo is Risk Vs. Reward balanced.  Would you try a mob knowing that at best you have a 20% chance to win?  Some would, some would not, but there is high risk.<br>
<br>
Personal solution to charm is make it immune to focus effects.  Verant already did something similiary with Cheal which would be too powerful with focus effects so they made it immune, Charm is similiar with focus effects there is not enough risk.  <br>
<br>
BTW enchanters have the worst self only mana regen ability.  The only spell an enchanter can use to regain mana that he/she cant cast on a group is Theft of Thought (New Dot Scryer too).  Druid, Mage, Necro, Wiz all have better self mana regen spells.     <br>
