Random other thoughts about this thread. <br>
<br>
I don't know about you guys, but I was soloing kael arena at level 60 with epic without much trouble, this was before I got VT gloves too. Bank area is a joke, arena was a bit of a challenge, but even multiple pulls were easily done with a bit of root net or bio orb action.<br>
<br>
As for the &quot;mages have no defense&quot; argument... What exactly do you call those expendable, loyal, cute balls of air/dirt/water/fire that follow us around and do everything (almost) we tell them to? You say your pet last 2 seconds against tier2 mobs? That's funny, I KILL tier 2 melee mobs with pet tanking, they don't live 2 sec, they live the whole damn fight. Would you like it if I pointed out that you didn't experience the game high enough to learn how to make your pet tank? I've soloed in HoH, dunno how your pets can die in 5 sec there. (don't take it as personnal, simply answering you the same way you answered goladus, if you get pissed at my attitude, look at yours toward him). <br>
<br>
Heck 3-4 mages can tank GODs in PoP. Case in point here. We had a TT raid lately with maybe 40 people including a lot of new recruits that didn't get the flag with rest of the guild when PoP opened. So we went back to PoNb to smack her. Now TT encounter isn't hard but there was a lot of people new to it, 2boxed and stuff so when the first wave of adds poped, there's was a bit of confusion and while we killed them all, we lost too many clerics and all our warriors in the process, and TT was turning on other tanks and we had no healer to keep them alive. At that point me and 3 other mages started chaining pets at TT at my command. Not only did this work, but it worked well. 3 mages pets held a slowed TT for quite a few minutes while reses were being done. Yes pets were getting killed pretty fast, but thanks in part to pet enrage, they lasted long enough so that 3 of us could keep 2 pets on her pretty much at all time. We ended up dragging corpse out and started over, but we could have held TT between 3 mages and maybe 1 slower to keep her slowed for an eternity (the 3 of us have pretty decent mana regen and mana pool ;p).<br>
<br>
You guys need to remind yourself that even the best tank will go down pretty hard against unslowed tier2+ mobs. Just like tanks need fast healing if the mob isn't slowed, our pets will too. But a maxed mage (like only the top chanters really can solo BoT mobs, only the top mages will be comparable) can make his pet tank pretty decent up to tier4 in PoP. My non-charmed pet has been main tank in groups in all the PoP zones up to but excluding elemental planes. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
